Terminalia (
Figs. 13–15
) moderately large; left surstylus and apical part of right epandrial lamella brown, otherwise yellow (
Fig. 12
). Right epandrial lamella rectangular (
Fig. 13
), apex with a notch, near base with a long seta, setae on apical part short. Cerci fused (
Fig. 14
). Left surstylus composed of 3 sclerites: the small left surstylus 1 bears 3 setae, one very long seta on a tubercle. Inner side of left surstylus with a few long fine seta.

– Antenna with postpedicel brownish apically and longer, at least 3 times as long as wide. Metanotum usually yellow (except 

